                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The totenmaske hit the same creature with two claw Strikes this turn and is still adjacent to it</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The totenmaske drains flesh from the creature's body. The creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 1} unless it succeeds at a @Check[fortitude|dc:25] save (sickened 2 and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 2} on a critical failure).</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "divine"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "0B1P5B28bQjlrwq9",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Living Form",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The totenmaske takes the appearance of a Medium or smaller humanoid creature. This is either their form from before they became undead or the form of the last creature they successfully drained with Drink Flesh.</p>\n<p>This doesn't change the totenmaske's Speed or the attack and damage bonuses for their Strikes but might change the damage type their Strikes deal (typically to bludgeoning).</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "concentrate",
                        "divine",
                        "polymorph"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "dgqwcM1PfX5sBXkv",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Shape Flesh",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>After spending 1 minute in contact with a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed], @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Unconscious], or willing creature, a totenmaske can reshape the target's face, causing flesh to cover vital features. The target can attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:25] save to resist; a critical success grants temporary immunity to Shape Flesh for 24 hours. Each time the totenmaske Shapes Flesh, they choose one feature: ears (target becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Deafened]), eyes (target becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Blinded]), mouth (target can't speak or eat), or nose (target can't smell). A creature with both its nose and mouth sealed can't breathe and begins to suffocate. Changes are permanent until reversed by removing this curse, but the sealed flesh can be surgically opened with a successful @Check[medicine|dc:25] check that takes [[/gmr 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds} and deals @Damage[1d6[slashing]] damage per round.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "curse",
                        "divine"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        }
